## âœ… `man_1_simple_shell`

```man
.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "July 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple Unix shell interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.RI [command ...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic Unix shell that reads user input, parses it, and executes commands.
It supports both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
* Executes commands with arguments
.TP
* Supports built-in commands: 
.B exit
and 
.B env
.TP
* Handles command path resolution via the PATH environment variable

.SH USAGE
.TP
Interactive mode:
.B ./hsh
.br
Then enter commands as you would in a normal shell.

.TP
Non-interactive mode:
.B echo "ls -l" | ./hsh

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.

.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B main.c
Entry point for the shell
.TP
.B shell.c
Shell execution loop and logic
.TP
.B path.c
Functions for PATH resolution

.SH AUTHORS
See the 
.B AUTHORS
file in the root of the repository.

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1)

